    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) reflects the use of one ASTM F1717 configuration; however, the quantitative output comparison criteria (E/uval < 1.96, <10% QoI difference) are satisfied across all three QoIs and all three independent FEA platforms, providing sufficient evidence that the model is fit for the intended regulatory use. The overall credibility evidence is judged adequate to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
